2 Garlic
1 tin Sweetcorn
1 sachet Coriander
1 packet Udon Noodles
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet Ginger Paste
1 Carrot
1 Asian Greens
1 packet Sweet Soy Seasoning
320 g Chicken Breast Strips
tbs brown sugar
sesame oil
water
1 drizzle olive oil
plain flour
soy sauce

• Boil kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water.
• Cook udon noodles over medium-high heat, gently stirring with a fork to separate, until tender, 1-2 minutes.
• Drain, rinse and set aside.

• Meanwhile, slice carrot into half-moons. Roughly chop Asian greens. Finely chop garlic. Drain sweetcorn (see ingredients). Cut chicken breast strips into 2cm chunks.
• In a small bowl combine the plain flour and a splash of water, then stir until smooth.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook sweetcorn and chicken, until chicken is cooked through, 4-5 minutes.
TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it is no longer pink inside.

• Add carrot, sweet soy seasoning, garlic and ginger paste to the pan and cook, tossing, until warmed through, 2-3 minutes.
• Add chicken-style stock powder, the soy sauce, brown sugar, water and flour mixture and bring to the boil. Simmer until slightly reduced, 2-3 minutes.
• Add cooked noodles, Asian greens and the sesame oil and stir until slightly wilted, 2-3 minutes. Season with pepper.

* Divide sweet soy chicken and corn soup between bowls. Tear over coriander. Enjoy!